commentPostTextItems.html: Australians have won the first match to lead the series 1-0. Bangladesh put up a good fight to make a match out of it inspite scoring just 195 runs. Aussies were at one stage 102 runs off 11 overs but Bangladesh fought back to pick up 6 wickets with the spinners bowling well. Razzaq picked up 3 wickets to bring them back into the match with excellent support from Rafique after Gilchrist blasted the opening bowlers. Hussey stayed on till the end to finish it off. Gilchrist was awarded Man-of-match for his all-round performance hitting 76 runs off 46 balls and also for his 5 victims behind the wicket. Please join us for the next match on Wednesday. Cheers and bye!
